We took full advantage of their HH menu. The wings are $1 each, minimum order of 5 wings, and you have the choice of soy garlic (the best) or hot &amp;amp; spicy. The wings are perfectly crispy on the outside and tender and juicy on the inside. The basket of truffle fries ($5) is nice to share. The fries are thick, crispy, and you can definitely taste the truffle. All of the soju cocktails ($6 each) are great. They have a easy to read menu and was quick with their service. </td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="722"></td><td class="line-content"><br/></td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="723"></td><td class="line-content">I got the bulgogi hot bowl and the steamed dumplings. Upon entry, we decided it&amp;#39;s trendy and hip with its rough plaster exposed concrete wall on one side and reclaimed wood on the other it&amp;#39;s bigger than it looks with a second level. </td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="735"></td><td class="line-content"><br/></td></tr><tr><td class="line-number" value="736"></td><td class="line-content">We ordered crispy tofu which was tasty but found the hard outer crust on the tofu way too thick and hard, the side of caramelized kimchi was tasty. We also ordered the barn special chicken boa, which I highly recommend! Soft squishy white roll stuffed with fried chicken and shredded cabbage! We also ordered a spicy pork stone bowl which is sizzling hot, is a mixture of whole grain rice, veggies and spicy pork (not that spicy), a bowl of hot soup and your choice of truffle fries, which we got or your choice of salad. The plates are perfect for sharing which is a great way to enjoy the variety of dishes here and avg price is about $15 per plate. <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>One of my all-time favorite dinner spots in all of NYC. This restaurant is kind of on the outskirts of Koreatown which is nice because there&amp;#39;s not as much foot traffic. While I usually bring dates here, my parents had been bugging me to bring them somewhere different than what they&amp;#39;re used to. As a kid, we never had anything more than the chinese restaurant down the street so I was super excited to bring them here. My mom was a little reluctant at first but after I ordered everything she realized we were in the right place.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>We ordered table bbq ribeye- super fresh, it would&amp;#39;ve been nice if the little stove&amp;#39;s heat was more even as it felt like I was cooking a lot of it on one side. Either way, super delicious. We also ordered some tapas dishes: fried asparagus, 2 orders of crispy chicken buns, fried dumplings, roasted veggies and soy garlic wings. My parents were ABSOLUTELY blown away by the buns and all of my choices are what I generally go with so I wasn&amp;#39;t surprised at all. Came before 6pm so got the wings half off which was nice. You can definitely end up spending a ton of money trying everything here but I 1000% recommend it if you&amp;#39;re looking for something different.<span class="html-tag">&lt;/span&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;div <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--div__373c0__1mboc u-space-b2 border-color--default__373c0__2oFDT</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;p <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--p__373c0__3Qnnj text__373c0__2pB8f comment__373c0__3EKjH text-color--normal__373c0__K_MKN text-align--left__373c0__2pnx_</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;span <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--span__373c0__3997G</span>" <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>Came after Phantom of the Opera and it was fun fusion for sure! Last call was around 10:30pm so it worked out for us, the service was also quick at that time. Started with the chicken wings, and they really were the perfect texture, doubley crispy on the outside, and tender on the inside. We ordered soy ginger and I wanted there to be a bit more sauce/flavor, but I would get the spicy version next time.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Next, we had the truffle rice cakes and cheese, which was so good! The combo of creamy cheeses and rice cakes was unique and yummy, it came out gooey and bubbly.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The bulgogi came as a mountain of meat, which was great. It was smoky and yummy, but didn&amp;#39;t come with rice, so just be aware. Definitely a big, shareable entree.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Lastly, we got the spicy charred chicken, which wasn&amp;#39;t our favorite. I love spicy food, but this felt spicy for the sake of spicy, and not for flavor per se. My friends couldn&amp;#39;t take more than a few bites (so be warned, actually kind of spicy!). <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>This was too much food for the three of us but we had a good amount of leftovers for later. The ambience was ~hip~ and fun and there was a cool moon light that lit the place up. Would recommend.<span class="html-tag">&lt;/span&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;div <span And I can&amp;#39;t quite pick out what it was. The restaurant staff was wonderful, very knowledgeable, patient and quick.  I had the bulgogi hot stone bowl, chicken buns and truffle fries. The food wad presented beautifully and very Instagram-worthy. It ticked all the boxes! But I had much higher expectations from a restaurants with as many raving yelp reviews as Barn Joo. class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--div__373c0__1mboc u-space-b2 border-color--default__373c0__2oFDT</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;p <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--p__373c0__3Qnnj text__373c0__2pB8f comment__373c0__3EKjH text-color--normal__373c0__K_MKN text-align--left__373c0__2pnx_</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;span <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--span__373c0__3997G</span>" <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>Came here on a Monday night after work for a quick meal with friends. We have heard so much buzz about this Korean gastropub we just had to try it! First off, the location is great, especially if you commute via train (it&amp;#39;s a 10 minute walk from Penn). <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Make a reservation, no matter what day of the week. The restaurant is two levels, and it started filling up around 6pm, as they have a happy hour menu. The four of us were seated, and our waiter brought us water and menus. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Their food options were so unique and trendy. We opted for a few appetizers, because they all looked delicious. We ordered the crispy chicken buns, calamari and Parmesan fries. Boy did the appetizers not disappoint!!!  They were fresh and super flavorful!<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>For our meals, we all ordered something different. I opted for the NY Bites, which was smoked beef and potatoes. It was alright, nothing be excited about. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Once i was time for dessert, we were excited. We ordered the cheesecake with fresh fruit, a churro bowl with vanilla ice cream, and the chocolate lava cake. They were delicious, and a big serving.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>All in all, the food was okay, but the appetizers took the cake. The prices are on the higher side, but that&amp;#39;s expected for a trendy, fresh Korean gastropub. Would want to try something new next time!! class="html-tag">&lt;/span&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;div <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--div__373c0__1mboc u-space-b2 border-color--default__373c0__2oFDT</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;p <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--p__373c0__3Qnnj text__373c0__2pB8f comment__373c0__3EKjH text-color--normal__373c0__K_MKN text-align--left__373c0__2pnx_</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;span <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--span__373c0__3997G</span>" <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>The wait wasn&amp;#39;t too bad for 7pm on a Saturday night. We were seated upstairs, it&amp;#39;s loud and noisy both downstairs and upstairs but filled with lots of energy. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Started off with crunchy tofu, veggie japchae, nutty green salad and a ginger limeade. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>We both walked all over and walked back and forth on the Brooklyn bridge so we came with an empty belly and parched too. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The limeade ginger was so refreshing and nicely quenched my thirst. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The crunchy tofu was nicely crispy and soft on the inside, lots of flavors, the fried kimchi garnish was a good balance to the crunchy tofu. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The veggie japchae was delicious, nice peppery kick and lots of great veggies. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The nutty salad was topped with sweet crunchy almonds and the dressing gave it great depth and flavor pops.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Wondering imagining how we could get one of these in Michigan, would be so great in Ann Arbor or in Detroit and would be a frequent haunt for me for certain. There&amp;#39;s nothing like it in MI at all. Maybe some food for thought to the owner. ;)<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>It&amp;#39;s a Monday night and we are back for more. We were seated right away, upstairs too, downstairs seems too chaotic for me. It&amp;#39;s before 7pm. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>We ordered the limeade ginger again, the crunchy tofu, nutty greens and this time trying out the truffle fries and the popcorn chicken. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The crunchy tofu didn&amp;#39;t disappoint and were just as good as Saturday night amidst the hustle and bustle of the weekend frenzy. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The popcorn chicken was also nice and crunchy and went nicely with the smoked sriracha BBQ sauce. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The nutty salad was as good as I recalled from Saturday night, but I did have to ask for more dressing as it was rather sparse on the coverage the first round. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The truffle fries didn&amp;#39;t meet my standards for truffle fries tonight. They smelled of truffle oil, only faintly when they were brought to the table, but I couldn&amp;#39;t taste the oil in any of the bites and the fries were over done for my liking. I like a nice golden yellow tint to my Idaho spuds. My hubby will eat any spuds since they are potatoes after all, but not me. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>I will be back again for some more crunchy tofu, nutty salad, popcorn chicken and some more adventures here in the future. Until my next visit NYC and Barn Joo. <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>Came to Barn Joo 35 for their happy hour (Monday - Friday, 4-6pm) as a group of 4. We took full advantage of their HH menu. The wings are $1 each, minimum order of 5 wings, and you have the choice of soy garlic (the best) or hot &amp;amp; spicy. The wings are perfectly crispy on the outside and tender and juicy on the inside. The basket of truffle fries ($5) is nice to share. The fries are thick, crispy, and you can definitely taste the truffle. All of the soju cocktails ($6 each) are great. We ordered Midtown Forsythia, Aloe Elixir, and Passionate Barn Joo. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The restaurant gets very busy so I recommend making a reservation through Yelp. Service is great and food gets served quickly. the back near the kitchen it is a tad bit more quiet.  <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>We ordered 5 dishes for the two of us.  We had a tempura based roll with an aioli.  Then a soft shell crab deep fried with home made tartar and a hint of truffle oil.  Then we had a bulgogi stone bowl followed by a crispy fried chicken bun and lastly their homemade vegetarian dumplings.  <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Highlights were the soft shell and the chicken bao.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span> The sauce on and texture of the bao made the dish.  The soft shell crab I would order it again then had a way to keep it crunchy without getting soggy.<span I&amp;#39;ve been eyeballing it for awhile but never had a chance to stop by. They don&amp;#39;t take reservations so I joined the waitlist via Yelp. I&amp;#39;m not sure if it&amp;#39;s a Yelp issue or a Barn Joo 35 issue but it was confusing that I mentioned to the hostess that I was on the waitlist and she had to check-in me in even though I hadnt received a notification yet. Not a big deal.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>I waited for about 45 minutes before my table for two was ready. My friend and I had a few beers and soju and then the bulgolgi, chicken wings, pork dumplings, popcorn chicken, sides of rice, and a few other things and all of it was excellent. <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>First order of business: If you&amp;#39;re reading this, then you likely have a Yelp account, and if you do, then make sure you check-in to Barn Joo 35 to get your free shochu shot (it&amp;#39;s a very tiny sample, and yup it was filled w/sugar, but it&amp;#39;s free). :) <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Barn Joo 35 is a trendy and yummy Korean &amp;#34;tapas&amp;#34; spot without all the rush of tourists and overload of foodies door-busting. Went on a Sunday evening with my parents and my husband on a visit to Koreatown. Keep in mind the dishes are tapas-sized, so it&amp;#39;s probably best to try multiple small dishes. I think we ordered 4-5 dishes altogether, which fared well amongst us all. But in all honesty, I can&amp;#39;t recall all the dishes we had, but the ones that stood out were the Garlic Soy Chicken Wings (super tasty), Bulgogi and Jap Chae. We also ordered the deep fried gyozas, which just felt a bit too heavy.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The tapas sizes compared to the prices being on the heftier side and the fact that I can&amp;#39;t remember all 5 dishes that we ordered qualify this place four stars rather than five. Just felt like we could&amp;#39;ve gotten more bang for our buck, with a bigger wow-factor!<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Service was business, as I class="html-tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;div <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--div__373c0__1mboc u-space-b2 border-color--default__373c0__2oFDT</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;p <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--p__373c0__3Qnnj text__373c0__2pB8f comment__373c0__3EKjH text-color--normal__373c0__K_MKN text-align--left__373c0__2pnx_</span>"&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;span <span class="html-attribute-name">class</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">lemon--span__373c0__3997G</span>" <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>Your very crowded Korean fusion with a long wait. The wait was about 30 minutes on a Friday evening although we join the Live waitlist so make sure you book a week in advance. The place is really crowded, very very crowded, but there is a second floor. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>We had the kimchi pancake, bulgogi stone pot, galbi-jjim, litchi and aloe soju cocktail. The good: litchi/aloe soju cocktail, kimchi pancake. The kimchi cake is thicker than your usual Korean pancake loaded with kimchi, you immediately notice it&amp;#39;s homemade and very unique. We loved both soju cocktail with uniquely cubed ice and blueberry in each. Both were not very sweet, but the balance between juice and soju was perfect. Another highlight was the rib stew (galbi-jjim). We loved how the ribs were very tender and the carrots/radish were well stewed. However, the rice noodle was placed at the very bottom and unfortunately did not absorb any sauce and therefore looked and tasted awful. The bulgogi pot was as expected, good but nothing to write home about.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The service was on par with other trendy Korean places in midtown. Price was also reasonable for the portion.<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>food 4/5<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>service 4/5<span <span class="html-attribute-name">lang</span>="<span class="html-attribute-value">en</span>"&gt;</span>I heard about this place for a while but finally had it now! <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>Please note this place is a Tapas Restaurant, so you know to not be as surprised as my friends and I when we saw the tiny plates. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>It&amp;#39;s another dimly-lit Korean cuisine restaurant serving alcoholic drinks and Korean dishes, which there are plenty of in Midtown. But personally, this might be slightly better in that they look out for their Yelpers with free shots upon check-in! The shot was pretty delicious too, nice and fruity!<span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The food is a hit or miss. Personally, I really enjoyed the $1 Happy Hour wings. The Soy Garlic wings were fried just right and were delicious, especially given the price. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>I thought the Truffle Rice Cake &amp;amp; Cheese was going to be good, but it was too heavy and mochi-like. I understand why this dish would be tiny. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>The Crunchy Tofu was not what I imagined. It was sweet, and just covered in that sauce. <span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;br&gt;</span>I would definitely go back here for the Happy Hour wings but avoid the tapas.<span class="html-tag">&lt;/span&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class="html-tag">&lt;div <span We also ordered a spicy pork stone bowl which is sizzling hot, is a mixture of whole grain rice, veggies and spicy pork (not that spicy), a bowl of hot soup and your choice of truffle fries, which we got or your choice of salad.
